2—habitat, western slopes of the equatorial Andes (Ecuador: Chimborazo Province) at altitudes about 1800 m; 3—host plant 
<taxonomicName authority="Kunth" authorityName="Kunth" box="[911,1175,1976,1998]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Acalypha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="padifolia">
<emphasis box="[911,1106,1976,1998]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Acalypha padifolia</emphasis>
Kunth
