<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,404,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from Latin 
<emphasis box="[792,853,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">apice</emphasis>
(apex) and 
<emphasis box="[986,1064,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">brunus</emphasis>
(brown) in reference to the color of the forewing with a distinctive brown apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
